<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-10-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="26" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d26">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894c.111/12: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-07T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October 7,
                                        1920—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>268. Referring to Department’s despatch No. 18 of June 24, 1920,
                            concerning temporary war-time passport control on the Japanese and
                            Russian railways please telegraph result of your conferences with your
                            colleagues in the premises.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>